#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn15"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn15:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 15 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 15 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn15:0.2"
msgid "Anumānasutta "
msgstr "Measuring Up "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, sc1
msgctxt "mn15:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
#. VAR: susumāragire → suṃsumāragire (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn15:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhaggesu viharati susumāragire bhesakaḷāvane migadāye. "
msgstr "At one time Venerable Mahāmoggallāna was staying in the land of the Bhaggas on Crocodile Hill, in the deer park at Bhesakaḷā’s Wood. "

msgctxt "mn15:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There Venerable Mahāmoggallāna addressed the mendicants: "

msgctxt "mn15:1.4"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn15:1.5"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied. "

msgctxt "mn15:1.6"
msgid "Āyasmā mahāmoggallāno etadavoca: "
msgstr "Venerable Mahāmoggallāna said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2, sc2
msgctxt "mn15:2.1"
msgid "“Pavāreti cepi, āvuso, bhikkhu: "
msgstr "“Suppose a mendicant invites "

msgctxt "mn15:2.2"
msgid "‘vadantu maṃ āyasmanto, vacanīyomhi āyasmantehī’ti, so ca hoti dubbaco, dovacassakaraṇehi dhammehi samannāgato, akkhamo appadakkhiṇaggāhī anusāsaniṃ, atha kho naṃ sabrahmacārī na ceva vattabbaṃ maññanti, na ca anusāsitabbaṃ maññanti, na ca tasmiṃ puggale vissāsaṃ āpajjitabbaṃ maññanti. "
msgstr "other mendicants to admonish them. But they’re hard to admonish, having qualities that make them hard to admonish. They're impatient, and don't take instruction respectfully. So their spiritual companions don’t think it’s worth advising and instructing them, and that person doesn’t gain their trust. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, sc3
msgctxt "mn15:3.1"
msgid "Katame cāvuso, dovacassakaraṇā dhammā? "
msgstr "And what are the qualities that make them hard to admonish? "

msgctxt "mn15:3.2"
msgid "Idhāvuso, bhikkhu pāpiccho hoti, pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gato. "
msgstr "Firstly, a mendicant has wicked desires, having fallen under the sway of wicked desires. "

msgctxt "mn15:3.3"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu pāpiccho hoti, pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gato—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:3.4"
msgid "ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (1) "
msgstr "This is a quality that makes them difficult to admonish. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "mn15:3.5"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu attukkaṃsako hoti paravambhī. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant glorifies themselves and puts others down. … "

msgctxt "mn15:3.6"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu attukkaṃsako hoti paravambhī—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:3.7"
msgid "ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (2) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "mn15:3.8"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu kodhano hoti kodhābhibhūto. "
msgstr "They’re irritable, overcome by anger … "

msgctxt "mn15:3.9"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu kodhano hoti kodhābhibhūto—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:3.10"
msgid "ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (3) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "mn15:3.11"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu kodhano hoti kodhahetu upanāhī. "
msgstr "They’re irritable, and hostile due to anger … "

msgctxt "mn15:3.12"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu kodhano hoti kodhahetu upanāhī—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:3.13"
msgid "ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (4) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "mn15:3.14"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu kodhano hoti kodhahetu abhisaṅgī. "
msgstr "They’re irritable, and stubborn due to anger … "

msgctxt "mn15:3.15"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu kodhano hoti kodhahetu abhisaṅgī—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:3.16"
msgid "ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (5) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
#. VAR: kodhasāmantā → kodhasāmantaṃ (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn15:3.17"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu kodhano hoti kodhasāmantā vācaṃ nicchāretā. "
msgstr "They’re irritable, and blurt out words bordering on anger … "

msgctxt "mn15:3.18"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu kodhano hoti kodhasāmantā vācaṃ nicchāretā—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:3.19"
msgid "ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (6) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
#. VAR: codito → cudito (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn15:3.20"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakaṃ paṭippharati. "
msgstr "When accused, they object to the accuser … "

msgctxt "mn15:3.21"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakaṃ paṭippharati—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:3.22"
msgid "ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (7) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "mn15:3.23"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakaṃ apasādeti. "
msgstr "When accused, they rebuke the accuser … "

msgctxt "mn15:3.24"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakaṃ apasādeti—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:3.25"
msgid "ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (8) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.96, sc11
msgctxt "mn15:3.26"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakassa paccāropeti. "
msgstr "When accused, they retort to the accuser … "

msgctxt "mn15:3.27"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakassa paccāropeti—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:3.28"
msgid "ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (9) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "mn15:3.29"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmeti, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti. "
msgstr "When accused, they dodge the issue, distract the discussion with irrelevant points, and display annoyance, hate, and bitterness … "

msgctxt "mn15:3.30"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmeti, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:3.31"
msgid "ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (10) "
msgstr " "

# NOTE: apadana has the root meaning of “reaping, harvest”, hence the more common sense of “story of past lives, i.e. deeds and their consequences”.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "mn15:3.32"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena apadāne na sampāyati. "
msgstr "When accused, they don’t accept the consequences of their deeds … "

msgctxt "mn15:3.33"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena apadāne na sampāyati—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:3.34"
msgid "ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (11) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "mn15:3.35"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu makkhī hoti paḷāsī. "
msgstr "They are offensive and contemptuous … "

msgctxt "mn15:3.36"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu makkhī hoti paḷāsī—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:3.37"
msgid "ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (12) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "mn15:3.38"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu issukī hoti maccharī. "
msgstr "They’re jealous and stingy … "

msgctxt "mn15:3.39"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu issukī hoti maccharī—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:3.40"
msgid "ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (13) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "mn15:3.41"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu saṭho hoti māyāvī. "
msgstr "They’re devious and deceitful … "

msgctxt "mn15:3.42"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu saṭho hoti māyāvī—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:3.43"
msgid "ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (14) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "mn15:3.44"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu thaddho hoti atimānī. "
msgstr "They’re obstinate and vain … "

msgctxt "mn15:3.45"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu thaddho hoti atimānī—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:3.46"
msgid "ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (15) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "mn15:3.47"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant is attached to their own views, holding them tight, and refusing to let go. "

msgctxt "mn15:3.48"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:3.49"
msgid "ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (16) "
msgstr "This too is a quality that makes them difficult to admonish. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "mn15:3.50"
msgid "Ime vuccantāvuso, dovacassakaraṇā dhammā. "
msgstr "These are the qualities that make them hard to admonish. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4, sc20
msgctxt "mn15:4.1"
msgid "No cepi, āvuso, bhikkhu pavāreti: "
msgstr "Suppose a mendicant doesn’t invite "

msgctxt "mn15:4.2"
msgid "‘vadantu maṃ āyasmanto, vacanīyomhi āyasmantehī’ti, so ca hoti suvaco, sovacassakaraṇehi dhammehi samannāgato, khamo padakkhiṇaggāhī anusāsaniṃ, atha kho naṃ sabrahmacārī vattabbañceva maññanti, anusāsitabbañca maññanti, tasmiñca puggale vissāsaṃ āpajjitabbaṃ maññanti. "
msgstr "other mendicants to admonish them. But they’re easy to admonish, having qualities that make them easy to admonish. They're accepting, and take instruction respectfully. So their spiritual companions think it’s worth advising and instructing them, and that person gains their trust. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5, sc21
msgctxt "mn15:5.1"
msgid "Katame cāvuso, sovacassakaraṇā dhammā? "
