msgctxt "mn15:5.46"
msgid "ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (15) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc36
msgctxt "mn15:5.47"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu asandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti anādhānaggāhī suppaṭinissaggī. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant isn’t attached to their own views, not holding them tight, but letting them go easily. "

msgctxt "mn15:5.48"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu asandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti, anādhānaggāhī suppaṭinissaggī—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:5.49"
msgid "ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (16) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc37
msgctxt "mn15:5.50"
msgid "Ime vuccantāvuso, sovacassakaraṇā dhammā. "
msgstr "These are the qualities that make them easy to admonish. "

# NOTE: Anumana seems to only occur twice in the EBTs, here and SN 22.36. There, BB accepts the sense “measure against”. It seems to me this meaning applies here. the passage specifically discusses, not an inference in general, but how one is to measure oneself against another. This, of course, reads straight from the etymology of the term. Moreover, this sense makes the whole sutta hang together better. The next section refers to paccavekkhana, i.e. “reflection”. So this section is about an external standard, the next section is about an inner standard. In later texts, especially Mil 6.4.1, anumana did indeed come to mean “inference”.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, sc38
#. VAR: anuminitabbaṃ → anumānitabbaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "mn15:6.1"
msgid "Tatrāvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ anuminitabbaṃ: "
msgstr "In such a case, a mendicant should measure themselves against another like this. "

msgctxt "mn15:6.2"
msgid "‘yo khvāyaṃ puggalo pāpiccho, pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gato, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo; "
msgstr "‘This person has wicked desires, having fallen under the sway of wicked desires. And I don’t like or approve of this person. "

msgctxt "mn15:6.3"
msgid "ahañceva kho panassaṃ pāpiccho pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gato, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti. "
msgstr "And if I were to fall under the sway of wicked desires, others wouldn’t like or approve of me.’ "

msgctxt "mn15:6.4"
msgid "Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘na pāpiccho bhavissāmi, na pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gato’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (1) "
msgstr "A mendicant who knows this should give rise to the thought: ‘I will not fall under the sway of wicked desires.’ … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc39
msgctxt "mn15:6.5"
msgid "‘Yo khvāyaṃ puggalo attukkaṃsako paravambhī, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:6.6"
msgid "ahañceva kho panassaṃ attukkaṃsako paravambhī, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn15:6.7"
msgid "Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘anattukkaṃsako bhavissāmi aparavambhī’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (2) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc40
